t followed the recipe exactly - the verdict from the family was that they were the best I'd ever made!</div></div></div></div> </article></div></div><div><div id="comment-wrapper-821486"><a id="comment-821486"></a><article class="comment"> <header class="comment__header"><div class="comment__author-picture"> <span class="comment__author-picture--no-login"></span></div><div class="comment__author-name"> <span class="username">Zubs</span></div><div class="comment__date"> 28th Dec, 2014</div> </header><div class="comment__text"><div class="field field-name-comment-body field-type-text-long field-label-hidden"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even">Tastes delicious BUT it certainly needs a few tweaks.
Reduce the quantity of milk, as the stated quantity makes dough way too sticky. Start with maybe 225ml & keep adding as needed.
I added the spices & fruits to the flour mix.
Increase spice to 2tsp cinnamon plus 1tsp allspice
To make it more "luxurious" I added more fruit.
Two proving worked perfectly for me.
I baked it for 15 mins only.</div></div></div></div> </article></div></div><div><div id="comment-wrapper-843516" class="indented"><a id="comment-843516"></a><article class="comment comment__indented-wrapper comment__indented-wrapper-1"><div class=" comment__indented comment__indented-1"> <header class="comment__header"><div class="comment__author-picture"> <span class="comment__author-picture--no-login"></span></div><div class="comment__author-name"> <span class="username">Littleleni</span></div><div class="comment__date"> 24th Mar, 2015</div> </header><div class="comment__rating-and-report-wrapper"><div class="comment__rating"><div class="rate-widget rate-widget-fivestar clear-block rate-processed"><div class="fivestar-bbcgoodfood"><div class="clearfix fivestar-widget-static fivestar-widget-static-vote fivestar-widget-static-5"><div class="star star-1 star-odd star-first"><span class="on">3.8</span></div><div class="star star-2 star-even"><span class="on"></span></div><div class="star star-3 star-odd"><span class="on"></span></div><div class="star star-4 star-even"><span class="on"></span></div><div class="star star-5 star-odd star-last"><span class="off"></span></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="comment__text"><div class="field field-name-comment-body field-type-text-long field-label-hidden"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even">Thanks! This was super helpful.</div></div></div></div></div> </article></div></div><div><div id="comment-wrapper-755546"><a id="comment-755546"></a><article class="comment"> <header class="comment__header"><div class="comment__author-picture"> <span class="comment__author-picture--no-login"></span></div><div class="comment__author-name"> <span class="username">michala2160</span></div><div class="comment__date"> 7th Apr, 2014</div> </header><div class="comment__text"><div class="field field-name-comment-body field-type-text-long field-label-hidden"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even">I use my breadmaker on the dough setting, I want to bake homemade bread but dont have the time and this takes all the hassle of kneading etc, and no messy hands. I melted the butter separately to the milk, I put the butter in the bread pan, after all the dry ingredients first, and a touch of the milk to get the dough going, then I added the milk little by little JUST enough to bring the dough altogether otherwise adding all of this milk might give you an unworkable dough. Also recommend adding more spice! When machine finished dough is already proved and just need to shape and leave for another 20 minutes to rise again.</div></div></div></div> </article></div></div></div></div></div></div> </section></div></div> <aside class="col span4"><div id="ad-mpu-premium-1-wide" class="ad-mpu-premium-1-wide"><div class="ad ad--mpu-premium-1-wide" id="ad-manager-ad-mpu_premium_1_wide-2fdceff003"><script type="text/javascript">Drupal.GPT.createSlot("ad-manager-ad-mpu_premium_1_wide-2fdceff003", function () {var m = Drupal.GPT.buildSizeMapping([[[0,0],[]],[[770,0],[[300,250],[300,600]]]]);var s = googletag.defineSlot(Drupal.GPT.unitPath(), m.define, "ad-manager-ad-mpu_premium_1_wide-2fdceff003").defineSizeMapping(m.mapping.build()).setTargeting("pos", ["mpu_premium_1"]).addService(googletag.pubads());});</script></div></div><div id="ad-mpu-premium-2"><div class="ad ad--mpu-premium-2-wide" id="ad-manager-ad-mpu_premium_2_wide-2d5789df73"><script type="text/javascript">Drupal.GPT.createSlot("ad-manager-ad-mpu_premium_2_wide-2d5789df73", function () {var m = Drupal.GPT.buildSizeMapping([[[0,0],[]],[[770,0],[[300,250],[300,251]]]]);var s = googletag.defineSlot(Drupal.GPT.unitPath(), m.define, "ad-manager-ad-mpu_premium_2_wide-2d5789df73").defineSizeMapping(m.mapping.build()).setTargeting("pos", ["mpu_premium_2"]).addService(googletag.pubads());});</script></div></div><div id="block-bbcgf-search-views-bbcgf-cc-alt-recipes" class="block block-bbcgf-search-views"><h2>Alternative recipes</h2><ul 